47
00:03:12,820 --> 00:03:17,500
<font color=#70DBDB>ARROW Season2Episode 02</font>

48
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:30,120
Mr.Queen,what are your mother's chances?

49
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:31,840
Is she on suicide watch?

50
00:03:33,710 --> 00:03:35,360
Mr.Queen,can you give us any comment?

51
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,680
It's not fair.

52
00:03:36,810 --> 00:03:37,830
They're not the ones on trial.

53
00:03:37,930 --> 00:03:41,410
That won't stop Jean Loring from using them as props to drum up sympathy.

54
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:42,820
You don't seem overly concerned.

55
00:03:42,940 --> 00:03:45,590
She confessed to being an accomplice on live television.

56
00:03:45,670 --> 00:03:48,270
Also sad that Malcolm Merlyn coerced here.

57
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:51,320
You have something,don't you?

58
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:54,280
I thought I was your co-counsel,Adam.

59
00:03:54,460 --> 00:03:57,330
If you're holding a trump card,don't you think maybe you should share it with me?

60
00:03:57,460 --> 00:03:59,170
It's going to be a good trial.

61
00:03:59,450 --> 00:04:01,170
Come on,let's get inside.

62
00:04:12,030 --> 00:04:13,400
You don't have to do this.

63
00:04:13,550 --> 00:04:14,540
Ivo says we do.

64
00:04:14,660 --> 00:04:15,850
Your friends are a danger to his men.

65
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:17,500
Go.Quick and quiet.

66
00:04:17,670 --> 00:04:19,370
Slade!Shado!Run!

67
00:04:32,930 --> 00:04:34,790
There's no one here.

68
00:04:36,530 --> 00:04:38,620
They must have moved on from their position.

69
00:04:38,830 --> 00:04:40,770
Chargers are placed.Here's the detonator.

70
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:43,460
Make sure they have no place to return to.

71
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:45,700
Go.

72
00:04:45,890 --> 00:04:47,140
And you.

73
00:04:48,310 --> 00:04:50,230
Now you're going to take us to the graves.

74
00:04:50,410 --> 00:04:52,450
Let's go.Get him up.

75
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,380
Let's get clear.

76
00:05:00,840 --> 00:05:02,340
Did you find the detonator?

77
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:03,220
Yes.

78
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:07,800
We were lucky.

79
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:09,720
I was lucky.

80
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:11,370
You were good.

81
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:13,130
Either way...

82
00:05:13,630 --> 00:05:15,290
They have Oliver.

83
00:05:15,650 --> 00:05:16,870
I'm going after him.

84
00:05:17,660 --> 00:05:19,140
Not alone.

85
00:05:19,970 --> 00:05:21,630
You can barely walk.

86
00:05:22,850 --> 00:05:24,960
All the more reason not to stay here.

87
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:27,680
Give them another chance at blowing me up.

88
00:05:34,710 --> 00:05:35,720
Are you two ok?

89
00:05:35,850 --> 00:05:37,010
I should be asking you that question.

90
00:05:37,140 --> 00:05:37,950
I'll be fine.

91
00:05:38,110 --> 00:05:39,410
You look like you have the flu.

92
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:42,140
If that's true,I shouldn't have wasted my time getting vaccinated.

93
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:44,980
Diggle,whatever it is,just go home.

94
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:46,940
Oliver,listen,I can take care of things.

95
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,880
No,we'll be fine,all right?

96
00:05:48,940 --> 00:05:51,000
Go rest.And don't make me call a cop.

97
00:05:51,190 --> 00:05:52,980
There are a few of them around here.

98
00:06:19,690 --> 00:06:24,750
...have been complicit in an undertaking with one horrible purpose...

99
00:06:25,190 --> 00:06:28,490
to destroy the Glades and everyone in it.

100
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:30,720
And it worked.

101
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:32,130
The Glades were destroyed.

102
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:34,130
Homes and lives were lost.

103
00:06:34,300 --> 00:06:36,350
All because of her actions.

104
00:06:36,620 --> 00:06:41,830
True,she had second thoughts; Remorse which compelled her to deliver this statement.

105
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:45,840
But on behalf of the 503 lives that were extinguished that day,

106
00:06:46,050 --> 00:06:49,870
I say,Moira Queen,your remorse comes too late.

107
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:56,210
For the last five years,under the threat for my life and the lives of my family...

108
00:06:56,820 --> 00:06:59,280
Why wouldn't those threats silence her?

109
00:06:59,460 --> 00:07:02,460
Why wouldn't Moira Queen be terrified?

110
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:06,280
Malcolm Merlyn killed her first husband,abducted her second.

111
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:08,600
Why wouldn't she be in fear for her life?

112
00:07:08,780 --> 00:07:10,660
For the lives of her children?

113
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:13,160
What would you do?

114
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:17,200
If it were your children in the crosshairs of a mad man's rage?

115
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:25,650
S.T.A.R.Lab's particle accelerator will be turned on right on schedule.

116
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:27,690
In other news,we have just received word

117
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:32,250
that both sides have now completed their opening statements in the Moira Queen trial.

118
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:34,500
Don't take this the wrong way,but you look disgusting.

119
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:36,630
Yeah,well,I don't feel great,Felicity.

120
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:39,140
Is there a right way to take that?

121
00:07:39,790 --> 00:07:40,890
You should go home.

122
00:07:41,030 --> 00:07:42,460
I am going.

123
00:07:42,620 --> 00:07:45,610
I just need to make arrangements for a replacement bodyguard.

124
00:07:45,820 --> 00:07:47,030
Did you get the flu shot?

125
00:07:47,210 --> 00:07:49,020
Personally,I never do.I know that I should.

126
00:07:49,250 --> 00:07:51,590
I just,I have this thing about needles.

127
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:53,280
All pointy things,really.

128
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:55,340
Which is ironic,considering who we work with.

129
00:07:55,470 --> 00:07:57,590
Yeah,it's not the flu,Felicity,it's more like...

130
00:07:57,830 --> 00:07:58,880
Dig!

131
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:02,700
Hello?

132
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:05,440
Are you here?

133
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,090
Here...

134
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,530
there...

135
00:08:08,670 --> 00:08:10,050
everywhere.

136
00:08:10,850 --> 00:08:14,740
So.How goes our little science project?

137
00:08:14,980 --> 00:08:16,030
Working like you said it would.

138
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,790
How wonderful.

139
00:08:19,010 --> 00:08:20,220
Ah,so listen.

140
00:08:20,580 --> 00:08:23,380
Doing the thing was 50,000.

141
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:28,120
Keeping quiet about it,I'm thinking it should be 50 more.

142
00:08:29,940 --> 00:08:32,340
Oh,I want word to spread.

143
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:34,740
It's kind of the whole objective,actually.

144
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:38,710
You see my point?

145
00:08:40,490 --> 00:08:43,350
You should know,I find post hoc negotiation...

146
00:08:43,530 --> 00:08:44,950
distasteful.

147
00:08:47,550 --> 00:08:51,490
Such a shame you won't get to see what your works have wrought,doctor.

148
00:08:52,090 --> 00:08:54,460
But soon,everyone else will.

149
00:08:55,350 --> 00:09:00,210
And they'll beg for it to end.

150
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,190
What the hell are you doing here?

151
00:09:11,350 --> 00:09:11,930
I heard you passed out.

152
00:09:12,060 --> 00:09:13,150
I told Felicity not to call you.

153
00:09:13,310 --> 00:09:16,480
Yeah,but before that,you said "gaw" and "thud," so I didn't take it very seriously.

154
00:09:16,590 --> 00:09:19,040
She was right to call me.Diggle,you need medical attention.

155
00:09:19,210 --> 00:09:20,350
He needs more than that.

156
00:09:20,490 --> 00:09:23,070
When Dig passed out,I sent a sample of his blood to a chemist I know at QC.

157
00:09:23,340 --> 00:09:25,850
The guy owes me a favor.Long story,I fixed his parking ticket.

158
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:27,850
Huh.I guess it's not that long.

159
00:09:27,990 --> 00:09:29,940
Felicity.The blood sample.

160
00:09:30,140 --> 00:09:31,960
Yeah.It came back positive...

161
00:09:32,170 --> 00:09:33,470
for trace amounts of Vertigo.

162
00:09:33,580 --> 00:09:34,930
I never used Vertigo before in my life.

163
00:09:35,050 --> 00:09:36,360
You were exposed to it somehow.

164
00:09:36,540 --> 00:09:37,730
Vertigo's in play again?

165
00:09:38,190 --> 00:09:41,580
When the Count recovered from his OD on Vertigo,he was sent to Iron Heights.

166
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:43,520
That got hit in the quake.

167
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:46,370
He got out the same way the Doll Maker did?

168
00:09:47,150 --> 00:09:49,010
And just like with the Doll Maker,

169
00:09:49,140 --> 00:09:52,170
prison officials worked overtime to keep the lid on the escape.

170
00:09:55,950 --> 00:09:57,040
I know what you're thinking.

171
00:09:57,170 --> 00:09:58,380
No,you don't.

172
00:09:58,690 --> 00:10:00,820
I made a choice not to put an arrow in this guy.

173
00:10:00,970 --> 00:10:02,700
And it was the right choice.

174
00:10:03,730 --> 00:10:05,400
There's no more killing.

175
00:10:06,370 --> 00:10:08,380
I worked this up to counteract the effects of Vertigo.

176
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:09,920
Give it to Diggle.I...

177
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:11,980
I need to get back to court.

178
00:10:12,110 --> 00:10:13,910
While I'm gone,just work up whatever you can

179
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:17,530
and figure out how Diggle got Vertigo in his system without his knowledge.

180
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:20,180
Ok.Go.

181
00:10:22,230 --> 00:10:26,060
When was the first time you heard about this so-called Undertaking?

182
00:10:26,340 --> 00:10:29,940
When everyone else did,when my mother gave the press conference.

183
00:10:30,050 --> 00:10:31,610
Doesn't seem like you took it too well.

184
00:10:31,740 --> 00:10:33,150
I was surprised.

185
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,980
Who wouldn't be?

186
00:10:39,150 --> 00:10:42,610
Uh,your mother was,um,immediately take into custody,

187
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:45,020
but I assume you went down to the precinct to see her?

188
00:10:45,310 --> 00:10:48,250
Um,actually I didn't see her until she was moved.

189
00:10:48,420 --> 00:10:49,630
To the prison.

190
00:10:50,110 --> 00:10:52,750
Do you remember when you visited her?

191
00:10:53,010 --> 00:10:54,710
Uh,not the exact date.

192
00:10:55,370 --> 00:10:58,070
It's ok,I have the visitor log here.

193
00:10:58,470 --> 00:10:59,840
October ninth.

194
00:11:00,570 --> 00:11:02,500
Five months later.

195
00:11:03,070 --> 00:11:04,420
Why so long?

196
00:11:04,780 --> 00:11:06,420
Um,I...I...

197
00:11:07,990 --> 00:11:09,490
Are you ok?

198
00:11:11,140 --> 00:11:12,510
An answer,please.

199
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:15,060
Why did it take you five months to visit your mother?

200
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:16,270
Your Honor,if I...

201
00:11:16,470 --> 00:11:17,940
No.I want to hear this.

202
00:11:19,460 --> 00:11:21,440
I needed time.

203
00:11:21,950 --> 00:11:23,070
I was...

204
00:11:23,230 --> 00:11:24,220
Angry.

205
00:11:24,370 --> 00:11:28,640
So angry,perhaps,that it took you five months to forgive her?

206
00:11:28,870 --> 00:11:30,650
It was complicated.

207
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:33,290
No.It's very simple.

208
00:11:33,450 --> 00:11:35,970
You blamed your mother for what she had done.

209
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,320
So why shouldn't the jury?

210
00:11:42,710 --> 00:11:47,100
Your Honor,we have no further questions for the...witness.

211
00:11:50,190 --> 00:11:51,560
Adam!

212
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,100
Where is it?

213
00:12:01,450 --> 00:12:02,990
Come on,where is it?!

214
00:12:05,180 --> 00:12:06,030
The Hosen,where is it?

215
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:10,260
- What? - The arrowhead.

216
00:12:10,390 --> 00:12:12,200
Every report said it was with these bodies.

217
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,050
You said you and your friends were here.

218
00:12:14,230 --> 00:12:15,550
Now,where is it?

219
00:12:17,270 --> 00:12:19,090
Take him outside.

220
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:22,010
Make him show you where his friends are hiding.

221
00:12:27,460 --> 00:12:28,560
Take us to them.

222
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:30,570
I don't know where they are!

223
00:12:32,660 --> 00:12:34,570
Tell me,or you lose your hand.

224
00:12:34,730 --> 00:12:36,600
Let us suggest another option.

225
00:12:36,780 --> 00:12:40,320
You hand the kid over to us,and we don't kill you all.

226
00:12:50,530 --> 00:12:52,060
Hey,are you ok?

227
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:55,100
Don't worry about me.

228
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:56,440
I can take it.

229
00:13:15,730 --> 00:13:17,520
Was that as bad as it seemed?

230
00:13:17,660 --> 00:13:18,980
Thea's testimony?

231
00:13:19,090 --> 00:13:20,410
It was a set-back.

232
00:13:20,690 --> 00:13:23,910
We were counting on her to... Humanize me.

233
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:25,310
Frankly,yes.

234
00:13:25,610 --> 00:13:27,220
And now we're going to have to go another way.

235
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:29,640
No. No,I told you,I won't testify.

236
00:13:29,770 --> 00:13:30,710
I know you did.

237
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,340
But now you have to.

238
00:13:32,450 --> 00:13:33,780
She's right,Mom.

239
00:13:35,970 --> 00:13:37,510
Jean,can you give us a minute?

240
00:13:37,860 --> 00:13:38,710
Yeah.

241
00:13:43,890 --> 00:13:45,440
I know what you're going to say.

242
00:13:46,060 --> 00:13:48,740
But if I testify,it will destroy our family.

243
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:51,830
And if your lawyer's right,you don't have a choice.

244
00:13:52,530 --> 00:13:55,600
Mom,secrets are what put you in this situation.

245
00:13:55,740 --> 00:13:58,070
Secrets and lies.

246
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:04,860
And now it is time to give the truth its day.

247
00:14:06,950 --> 00:14:10,420
Now,I don't want us to lose sight of the other major event in court today.

248
00:14:10,610 --> 00:14:13,490
Was there any indication of Adam Donner being ill?

249
00:14:14,070 --> 00:14:17,590
No,there was very little warning before Mr.Donner collapsed to the ground.

250
00:14:17,790 --> 00:14:20,200
I've spoken to several people that were in the courtroom with me...

251
00:14:21,050 --> 00:14:22,580
How are you feeling?

252
00:14:23,450 --> 00:14:24,530
Fine.

253
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:25,930
You have a lousy poker face,Diggle.

254
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:27,520
Did he take the antidote?

255
00:14:27,660 --> 00:14:28,580
Didn't work.

256
00:14:28,790 --> 00:14:30,230
The Count must have futzed with his recipe.

257
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:32,600
Heard what happened with Donner at the court,and with Thea.

258
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:34,950
How is she?

259
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,500
Going to be fine.

260
00:14:37,230 --> 00:14:39,590
Your poker face isn't much better than mine,Oliver.

261
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,710
Hello,Starling City.

262
00:14:43,970 --> 00:14:45,040
Felicity!

263
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,500
Miss me?

264
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:49,830
Many of you have noticed that you're not feeling quite like yourselves...

265
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:51,310
He's taken over all the local station feeds.

